The paper discusses explainable artificial intelligence (XAI) and focuses on a popular method called Layer-wise Relevance Propagation (LRP) in the context of visual object detection using feedforward neural networks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of computer science related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), neural networks (cs.NE), and natural language processing (cs.CL) as these are the areas where XAI and LRP are commonly used.
